# FormForge Monorepo

Form builder SaaS. **Migrating** from Next.js Route Handlers to FastAPI + Next.js monorepo.

## Layout

| Path | Purpose | Status |
|------|---------|--------|
| `src/` | Next.js UI + interim APIs | **Current** |
| `frontend/` | Next.js frontend | **Target** (split from `src/`) |
| `backend/` | FastAPI REST API | **Target** (replaces `src/app/api/`) |
| `docs/` | Architecture, SDLC handoffs | Active |
| `.cursor/agents/` | SDLC pipeline agents | Active |

Read `docs/architecture.md` before structural or cross-layer changes.

## Stack boundaries

- **New API work** → `backend/` when it exists; otherwise `src/app/api/` for fixes only
- **UI / builder / dashboard** → `src/` (later `frontend/`)
- **Shared types** → colocate per layer; avoid duplicating business logic in the web app
- **DB** → `src/db/` today; moves with FastAPI migration

## API domains

Auth, forms CRUD, fields, schema, responses, analytics, public forms — see `docs/architecture.md` migration table and root `README.md` API Reference.

## Commands

- Web (now): `npm run dev`, `npm run build`, `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck` from repo root
- DB: `npm run db:migrate`, `npm run db:seed`
- API tests (future): `pytest` from `backend/`
